MPLS Concept	Real-World Analogy	              Role in the Network
Packet	      Package	Data being transported
Label	        Barcode on the box	               Fast identifier for forwarding
Tunnel ID	    Delivery Route Number	              Identifies the LSP path
FTN	          Dispatch desk decision	           FEC → Label stack + Tunnel ID (Ingress LER)
ILM	          Label scanner at sorting hubs	     Incoming label → NHLFE
NHLFE	        Sorting/forwarding instructions	   What to do with the packet (next hop, label action)
LSR	          Sorting hub	Does                   label switching
Egress LER	  Last-mile delivery office          	Pops label and forwards to IP destination
